The Department of Education has released a state-by-state breakdown of funding for colleges and universities provided in the American Rescue Plan. This funding, provided through the Higher Education Emergency Relief Fund, is one of the largest one-time infusions of funding ever provided to higher education institutions. At least half of the funds are expected to be used for direct financial relief to students. These funds have already been utilized by colleges and universities across the country to support students and ensure continued learning during the COVID-19 pandemic. The impact of these funds has been significant. The article includes a factsheet for each state/territory detailing the funding allocated.